Polish Stocks: Lotos, Orlen, PGE, Polimex, TVN Move in Warsaw

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-08-26T13:20:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/polish-stocks-lotos-orlen-pge-polimex-tvn-move-in-warsaw.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index declined 19.01,
or 0.8 percent, to 2,295.32 at 2:42 p.m. in Warsaw, falling for
the first time in three days and trimming this week’s advance to
1.9 percent.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  PGE SA (PGE PW) gained 0.12 zloty, or 0.6 percent, to 19.94
zloty, taking its advance this week to 3.9 percent. Poland’s
biggest power producer was added to ING Groep NV’s list of “top
picks” in central  Europe .  PKN Orlen SA (PKN PW), Poland’s biggest oil company, slid
for a second day, retreating 0.27 zloty, or 0.7 percent, to
36.01 zloty.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  , the second-largest
refiner, lost 0.55 zloty, or 1.8 percent, to 30.1 zloty, its
fourth day of declines. Oil fell on speculation U.S. measures to
revive growth will fall short of expectations and that potential
fuel shortages caused by Hurricane Irene might be limited.  Polimex-Mostostal SA (PXM)  , Poland’s second-largest
construction company, sank 0.04 zloty, or 2.1 percent, to 1.84
zloty, heading for the lowest close in almost six years. KBC
Securities lowered its price estimate for the stock by 38
percent to 1.7 zloty and maintained its “sell” recommendation.  TVN SA (TVN)   declined 0.42 zloty, or 3 percent, to 13.43
zloty, falling for the first time this week as UniCredit SpA cut
its 12-month price projection for Poland’s biggest television
network by 16 percent to 14.7 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw at 
 pkozlowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
